    "non_goals": [
      "No model picker on the join/seat page; it stays provider-only.",
      "No attempt to set/control the model for MCP connections; the client decides and we only display it.",
      "The per-agent model stays optional; agents are not re-coupled to a mandatory model."
    ],
    "acceptance_criteria": [
      "A user can set an optional preferred model on an agent's settings page (advanced), choosing only from PROVIDER_MODELS.",
      "On a machine connection, the connector runs the agent's preferred model when it matches the seat's chosen provider; else the server's per-provider default; the connector built-in default is only a last resort.",
      "The connector verifies each model it would run with a cheap test call and reports pass/fail plus error text; the website shows per-model status (checking / verified / cannot-run with a reason).",
      "Verification results are cached and re-tested only on change or periodic refresh, never every poll.",
      "A model failure during a real turn surfaces the reason on connection/agent status; any forced fallback move is clearly tagged with why, never a silent HOARD.",
      "MCP seats show 'runs your client's model' read-only and ignore the preferred-model field.",
      "The join page remains provider-only."
    ],
    "checklist": {
      "goal": "Let a user optionally pick a specific AI model per agent and have it run reliably on machine connections, with the model decision living server-side, verified on the user's own machine before it matters (fail-fast), and any failure surfaced clearly so the user can fix it. MCP play is unaffected: the client's own model is used and shown read-only.",
      "audience": "Bot operators who run agents via a machine connection (the always-on connector) and want control over which model plays; the design must also stay correct and non-misleading for operators who play via MCP clients.",
      "constraints": "Server-rendered, SSE/HTMX fragments, mobile, async app. Repo constitution: full types, no suppressions, fail-loud/no swallowed errors, specific exceptions, tests for app/engine, focused filenames. Connector deploys by copy to ~/.agentludum + launchd restart (not by merge). Only the local connector can verify a model against the user's CLI login. Reuse: model_for_provider (app/engine/model_provider_match.py), provider_for_model + PROVIDER_MODELS (app/config.py), provider-readiness pattern (app/engine/provider_readiness.py, connection_health.py), connector self-report (/api/agent/report-pid)."
    },
